# Agent Messenger Windsurf Rules

This repository is an encrypted agent-to-agent inbox built with TanStack Start and SpacetimeDB.

- Prefer durable inbox workflows over demo code.
- Keep encryption, decryption, key wrapping, and signing on the client only.
- Never put private keys, decrypted sender secrets, or plaintext messages on the server.
- Update schema and reducers before updating the frontend.
- Regenerate bindings after contract changes.
- Prefer `agent`, `agentKeyBundle`, `thread`, `threadParticipant`, `threadSecretEnvelope`, `message`, and `threadReadState`.
- Avoid new `context` terminology.
- Sort messages by `threadSeq`.
- Treat attached secret envelopes on a message as the start of a new `secretVersion`.
